data.chText: （电路的）开关，闸，转换器
data.enText: a small device that you press or move up and down in order to turn a light or piece of electrical equipment on and off

data.chText: 电灯开关
data.enText: a light switch

data.chText: 通断开关
data.enText: an on-off switch

data.chText: 那是在过去，还没有到开关一响就有电的时代。
data.enText: That was in the days before electricity was available at the flick of a switch .

data.chText: 我按哪个开关就能把它关了？
data.enText: Which switch do I press to turn it off?

data.chText: 扳动开关
data.enText: to throw a switch (= to move a large switch)

data.chText: （尤指突然彻底的）改变，转变
data.enText: a change from one thing to another, especially when this is sudden and complete

data.chText: 轻重缓急的改变
data.enText: a switch of priorities

data.chText: 第一个孩子出生后她就从全职工作改为兼职工作。
data.enText: She made the switch from full-time to part-time work when her first child was born.

data.chText: 政策的转变
data.enText: a policy switch

data.chText: （铁路的）转辙器，道岔
data.enText: the points on a railway/railroad line

data.chText: （细软）枝条；鞭子
data.enText: a thin stick that bends easily

data.chText: 马鞭
data.enText: a riding switch

data.chText: （使）改变，转变，突变
data.enText: to change or make sth change from one thing to another

data.chText: 我们正在转用新的发票制度。
data.enText: We're in the process of switching over to a new system of invoicing.

data.chText: 按这两个键就可以在屏幕上的文件之间进行切换。
data.enText: Press these two keys to switch between documents on screen.

data.chText: 你们什么时候调动工作的？
data.enText: When did you switch jobs?

data.chText: 交换；掉换；转换；对调
data.enText: to exchange one thing for another

data.chText: 最后两门考试的日期掉换了。
data.enText: The dates of the last two exams have been switched.

data.chText: 我看出来你把家具重摆了。
data.enText: I see you've switched the furniture around (= changed its position) .

data.chText: 要是把我的杯子跟她的换了，你认为她看得出来吗？
data.enText: Do you think she'll notice if I switch my glass with hers?

data.chText: 调班；临时掉换工作时间
data.enText: to do sb else's job for a short time or work during different hours so that they can do your job or work during your usual hours

data.chText: 下个周末我不能上班——咱俩调个班好不好？
data.enText: I can't work next weekend─will you switch with me?

data.chText: 你找着能跟你调班的人了吗？
data.enText: Have you been able to switch your shift with anyone?
switch off

data.chText: 不再想着；不再注意；失去兴趣
data.enText: to stop thinking about sth or paying attention to sth

data.chText: 我听见“足球”两个字就腻味。
data.enText: When I hear the word ‘football’ I switch off (= because I am not interested in it) .

data.chText: 只有在我们外出度假的时候，他才真正无牵无挂。
data.enText: The only time he really switches off (= stops thinking about work, etc.) is when we're on vacation.
switch off/on
switch sth↔off/on

data.chText: 关 / 开（电灯、机器等）
data.enText: to turn a light, machine, etc. off/on by pressing a button or switch

data.chText: 你离开的时候请把灯关了。
data.enText: Please switch the lights off as you leave.

data.chText: 这东西怎么开？
data.enText: How do you switch this thing on?
switch over
switch sth↔over

data.chText: 换台；换频道
data.enText: to change stations on a radio or television

ex.chText: 玛丽同露西交换了外套。
在会上，双方就此问题交换了意见。
ex.enText: Both sides exchanged their opinions on the issue at the meeting.

synonyms.bx: 通常指互相交换同类东西。

ex.chText: 作为经理，他经常与员工交换意见。
ex.enText: As a manager, he often interchanges ideas with his workers.

ex.chText: 这两个朋友每周都有信件往来。
ex.enText: The two friends interchange letters each week.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指交流思想、信息或交换位置等。

ex.chText: 咱俩的玻璃杯对调了——这个是我的。
ex.enText: Our glasses have been switched/exchanged - this is mine.

ex.chText: 你愿意用你的马换我的汽车吗？
ex.enText: Will you switch/exchange your horse for my car?

synonyms.bx: 多用于口语，常可与 exchange 换用，但侧重于调换之意。

ex.chText: 他经常通过电话或网络进行交易。
ex.enText: He usually trades by phone or online.
She traded her books for his CDs.

synonyms.bx: 尤指买卖货物，也可表示交换物品。

trans: 不再注意；不再想着；不再担忧

tr: the act of changing one thing or position for another
example: his switch on abortion cost him the election

tr: two defensive players shift assignments so that each guards the player usually guarded by the other
a flexible implement used as an instrument of punishment
control consisting of a mechanical or electrical or electronic device for making or breaking or changing the connections in a circuit
railroad track having two movable rails and necessary connections
used to turn a train from one track to another or to store rolling stock
hairpiece consisting of a tress of false hair
used by women to give shape to a coiffure
an event in which one thing is substituted for another
example: the replacement of lost blood by a transfusion of donor blood

tr: reverse (a direction, attitude, or course of action)
change over, change around, as to a new order or sequence
make a shift in or exchange of
lay aside, abandon, or leave for another
example: switch to a different brand of beer

tr: flog with or as if with a flexible rod
cause to go on or to be engaged or set in operation
exchange or give (something) in exchange for

value.def: A switch is a small control for an electrical device which you use to turn the device on or off.

example.ex: Leona put some detergent into the dishwasher, shut the door and pressed the switch.
example.tran: 利昂娜将一些清洁剂放入洗碗机，关上门后按了开始键。

value.def: If you switch to something different, for example to a different system, task, or subject of conversation, you change to it from what you were doing or saying before.

example.ex: Estonia is switching to a market economy...
example.tran: 爱沙尼亚正在向市场经济转轨。

example.ex: The law would encourage companies to switch from coal to cleaner fuels...
example.tran: 该法律将鼓励企业转而使用比煤更加清洁的能源。

example.ex: The encouragement of a friend spurred Chris into switching jobs.
example.tran: 在一位朋友的鼓励下，克理斯换了工作。

example.ex: New technology made a switch to oil possible...
example.tran: 新技术使得转而使用石油成为可能。

example.ex: The spokesman implicitly condemned the United States policy switch.
example.tran: 发言人含蓄地谴责了美国政策上的转变。

example.ex: ...a professional man who started out in law but switched over to medicine.
example.tran: 开始学法律后转而从医的专业人士

value.def: If you switch your attention from one thing to another or if your attention switches, you stop paying attention to the first thing and start paying attention to the second.

example.ex: My mother's interest had switched to my health...
example.tran: 母亲转而关注起我的健康来。

example.ex: As the era wore on, she switched her attention to films.
example.tran: 随着这个时代慢慢过去，她把目光投向了电影业。

value.tran: 转移(注意力);(注意力)转变

value.def: If you switch two things, you replace one with the other.

example.ex: In half an hour, they'd switched the tags on every cable...
example.tran: 半个小时内，他们就给每根电缆都换了标签。

example.ex: The ballot boxes have been switched.
